nodes.documentation:
Main container contract which inherits all handler contracts
Logic is seperated out in to multiple contracts for readabilty and maintainability
 - Handler functions - Each of business entity functions are put in separate contracts - BankHandler, AdminHandler
 - Types - All custom types/struct are defined in the Types contract. Other contract will inherit Types if they need to use custom types.
 - DataStorage - All permanant storage varaibles are declared here. This contract can be shared between other contracts by inherting it.
 - AccessControl - All modifiers related to access, permission and authentication is defined here.
 - Helpers - Utiltites functions defined here

nodes.name: KYC

params: {string} _hash Hash of the customer's ID submitted for KYC
{address} _bankEthAddress The ethAddress of the bank issuing this request

addKycRequest(string,string).return: {bool}        True if this function execution was successful

params: {address} bankAddress Address of the bank to get the details
{address} bankAddress Address of the bank to get the rating
{string} bankAddress returns tuple with n lists where n corresponds to fields of KYC_Request struct. Each of the list are assosicated accross each other with index
{string} password password of the customer or '0' if no password is set
{address} bankAddress Address of the bank to be upvoted
{string} _userName Name of the customer to be upvoted

viewCustomer(string,string).return: {Customer} The customer struct as an object

addBank(string,string,address).notice: Adds bank to banks mapping and bank's address to bankAddresses list

addKycRequest(string,string).notice: Record a new KYC request on behalf of a customer The sender of message call is the bank itself

getAccessHistory(string).notice: Get the last bank which validated the cutomer data

getBankRequests(address).notice: Gets the list of each fields of kyc requests filtered for a bankAddress.

modifyCustomerPassword(string,string,str.notice: Modify the password of the customer whos has an existing password

removeBank(address).notice: Removes bank from banks mapping and remove bank's address to bankAddresses list

removeCustomer(string).notice: Remove customer from customer mapping and remove customer name from customerNames

removeKYCRequest(string,string).notice: Remove KYC request from kycRequests mapping and remove kyc data hash from customerDataList

setCustomerPassword(string,string).notice: Set password to protect customer data

upVoteBank(address).notice: Add a new upvote from a bank to another bank. caller should be a bank.

upvoteCustomer(string).notice: Add a new upvote from a bank to a customer
